CatDescriptText: Related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 21, 1965, pg. 7, reads: "Mardi[e] Gras Theme will be used for the annual charity ball given by the D.I. Club. Members hope that guests will come in costume, or at least en masque.  Here are three fascinating D.I. members ready for the March 7 ball at the Hilton.  There will be a parade preceding the ball, and two bands to dance by.  It just should be the most exciting affair of the season. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three D.I. Club members wearing costumes, including woman on left, possibly Nelley Barron,  wearing a satin mermaid skirt with tulle hem, sequined bodice, and dark hat with feathers, gathered around sofa in interior for the D.I.'s annual charity ball, another version
